cafes.name: Comfort & Joy Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 615 S Nevada Ave, Colorado Springs, CO 80904, USA

text.text: Lovely cats AND wonderful staff. We got to meet sunny, dan, louie, gypsy, moo, and ruby. It was nap time so the cats were very chill, and it was so sweet to be able to pet them while they slept. They would curl towards our hands or come and hang out next to us if we sat on the couch. A great place to hang out and get to know cats before adopting.

Best little cat cafe in town! Anywhere we go, me and my family like to support the local cats. Going to this cat cafe not only do you get some time with the kitties but you are also helping feed and rescue local cats that need homes. The two attendants we met today were so attentive and kind. We will definitely return
A beautiful cafe with dedicated and kind staff. They are doing great work at the Comfort & Joy Cat Cafe! So far since opening in September of 2024, they have already adopted out 21 kitties!

cafes.name: The Biscuit Factory Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 12 S 25th St, Colorado Springs, CO 80904, USA

text.text: I love coming to the Biscuit Factory and spending time hanging out with the cats in a beautiful Old Colorado City building. It‚Äôs $11 per hour and you get a soft drink, coffee or tea with admission. It‚Äôs hard to not fall in love with every cat that comes through here. There are plenty of toys to play with the cats, or have a sleepy cat just come take a nap on your lap or enjoy being held in your arms if you‚Äôre lucky enough! I can see every cat here is  very loved and taken care of. This is a wonderful hang out for cat lovers.

Adorable place and relaxing spot to relax for $11 entry fee per person (including kids). It's not a "cafe" though as you would expect especially if you've been to ones in places like Japan. It's more akin to an interactive cat adoption center that allows you to just hang out with the cats for a fee. Can't really dine in and order real food ü§î

Cats are well taken care of and it's a perfect place to pick a new friend to adopt if you're looking for a new feline companion üêà‚Äç‚¨õÔ∏è

Loved it! The cats were all entertaining and so sweet. Cute, calm and relaxing atmosphere. It was $11 to get in for one hour. I do wish they had more drink choices or maybe a nice self serve type area with bigger selection. But I‚Äôll definitely be back to enjoy sweet kitty time!

cafes.name: the bashful cat
cafes.address: 615 Maple St, Colorado Springs, CO 80903, USA

cafes.name: Teddy Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 39 E Florida Ave, Denver, CO 80210, USA

text.text:
I‚Äôve been to quite a few cat cafes all over the states, and Teddy Cat is by far the cleanest and most welcoming one I‚Äôve been to. It‚Äôs a must visit if you‚Äôre an animal lover in Denver and beyond! You can tell how much the owner/staff cares about the well-being of each cat that comes in, and they work really hard to find the best homes for each one. There‚Äôs also tons of unique merch that makes great stocking stuffers and gifts!

There‚Äôs no doubt that each kitty is truly loved here which is the most important thing :) can‚Äôt recommend enough!

Teddy Cat Cafe is a great owner operated cat caf√©! We got to spend time with adorable cats ranging from kittens to seniors‚Äîwe loved it. The atmosphere was inviting and cozy‚Äîaided by great conversation and coffee. They have a wide selection of merch, of which I went overboard on‚Äîbut that‚Äôs on me. Awesome place, recommend it to anyone‚Äîlocal and visitors
alike.

Everything about this place is amazing!! It was my first time at a Cat Cafe, and another cat-loving friend took me as my birthday date. You go in and pay for a playdate with all the kitties, and you get a complimentary serve-yourself coffee or tea while you are there. There are some rules, and they are all absolutely reasonable. TONS of goodies to look at while you pet and play. I wasn't there to adopt, but of course many visitors are there to find a furry forever friend.

Yes, it takes time for the cats to come up to you, but remember, you are a STRANGER in their space. The cats were lovely and fun to be around. The cafe was quiet and clean.  Props to the employees educating kids on how to properly interact with the kitties.

HIGHLY recommend for anyone needing a ‚ÄúPick me up‚Äù. My 11 y/o has been asking to go and today was the perfect gloomy day for cuddles. It was just us in there for a good hour and ALL of the cats were curious and playful! Drinks are available as well as many cat goodies. Lots of cat games to play. We decided to make it a monthly stop until we are ready for a third cat!

We had the best time at the Halloween pumpkin carving event! The staff was so friendly and the kittens were adorable. As a couple with no kids, our favorite time to hang at the cafe is weekdays after 5pm ‚Äî it‚Äôs super quiet so you get more play time with the cats üêà

Quick trip to Denver, staying in a downtown hotel. Wanted coffee, found Roostercat and off I went.

First, the walk to it was nothing but epic, taking me by the capital and so many beautiful museums and more. Just the atmosphere of my short journey here was well worth it.

The atmosphere at Roostercat was spot on as well. Loved the outdoor fireplace, a perfect place for stores apparently. üòÅ The music setting the ideal ambience. And the artwork just perfect for a shop like this.

Loved my ice latte and would drink it again and again.

Great stop whether coming from downtown or just looking for good coffee. The rest of the menu looked yummy as well. Awesome vibe overall!

The local oatmilk they have here is absolutely delicious, definitely worth the extra price. The atmosphere and ambiance is so chill and relaxed. I was able to get so much writing done and felt so welcomed by the staff. Will definitely be returning!

I LOVED it here. The atmosphere is exactly what I'm always looking for in cafes. The coffee was great - I went out on a limb and got the monkey fist latte (which has banana) and it was so so good. Also, they had a vegan burrito which was great also. This cafe also sells art prints and some thrifted clothes which is great. There's plenty of seating as well. Overall, this is one of the best cafes I've been to !

You can tell that the cats here are very well cared for and loved by the staff! The staff is very knowledgeable about the cats in their care and shared each cat‚Äôs story and name. Overall, it was a really fun way to spend our time in downtown Loveland!

My boyfriend and I were looking to adopt a cat and the Noco cat cafe was the perfect place to meet so many different kitty personalities. We adopted ‚ÄúTawney‚Äù and she has been such a wonderful addition. The folks working and running the facility did such an amazing job and were very helpful in letting us know the names of each cat, and helping put her in the carrier quickly for her travel home with us. They do a great job making sure each cat goes to a safe and loving home. Thank you so much to the cat cafe ü•∞

Love the NoCo Cat Cafe, can enjoy a nice beverage and cats.  The owners are great, very friendly and their passion for the felines is unmatched.  Anytime I am in the area, I must stop in with my CSU student daughter.  Thankfully, I have control, or I‚Äôd have a dozen cats at home!

cafes.name: Purrfect Pause Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 5290 Arapahoe Ave Unit E, Boulder, CO 80303, USA

text.text:
We absolutely love Purrfect pause. Not only are the cats fixed, they have all their vaccinations and are socialized with other cats and people. We adopted this Purrfect little angel and couldn‚Äôt be happier. They gave us a little adoption kit and all of the resources to make sure she is happy, healthy, and has a smooth transition. We will definitely be returning to the cat cafe in the future
.üêæü§çüêæü©∂üêæü§ç

I love this place! I‚Äôve been here 3 times now and all three times went perfectly! The staff are very kind and respectful, the cats are very cute (and all mostly up for adoption too!), and just a wonderful place to de-stress for an hour! s(=^‚Ä¢.‚Ä¢^=)‚ô°

The most wonderful cat cafe. The staff are incredibly caring and supportive. Both my cats are from here (from the same foster Mom, Jessica) and both are the best cats in the world. Couldn‚Äôt recommend more!

cafes.name: Alleycat Coffee House
cafes.address: 120 1/2 W Laurel St A, Fort Collins, CO 80524, USA

text.text: LOVE the location since it's on the second floor. Seems exclusive and cool. Great service. Great coffee. HORRIBLE playlist playing when we went by. Top 40 stuff from the 90s and 00s.....and it played Michael Jacksons smooth criminal twice within a 20 minute period! There should be college radio playing!!! Independent tunes. Singer/Songwriter stuff....Anything other than what was playing :/

Pros: Delicious food and drinks, friendly staff, and great atmosphere.

Cons: Food *can* take a very, very long time to come out due to small preparation space and low number of employees. No parking lot, so you have to find street parking.

Info: This is a very popular spot during the work week, so if you come in during the day M-F, be prepared to wait for seating to open up due to the large number of students that come here between classes. This is a seat-yourself establishment and there is no table service.

The vibe of this place is incredible but sometimes the music is too loud, especially for studying. I have noise canceling headphones and really dont mind a bit of background noise but they get overpowered by the tunes. Otherwise, amazing! Great selection of tea, food, and the art on display (and for sale) contributes to a fantastic atmosphere.

cafes.name: Cat's on Main
cafes.address: 260 W Main St, Cedaredge, CO 81413, USA

text.text: Cat's is a great little coffee shop with many tasty options. Their prices are comparable to other coffee places. The atmosphere is homey and inviting.

A delightful little place with a delightful hostess, exceptional coffee and lots of good munchies including breakfast bagels, muffins and burritos. Most of the store is given to displays of local arts crafts and doodads, and I like the many note cards.
Heal local coffee shop with a new friendly owner and wonderful staff.  The sausage breakfast sandwiches with pepper jelly are really good and affordable.
